<div class="container col-md-10">
  <p class="mt-5">Welcome to rules and help page dear <%= current_user.name %>! </p>

  <p class="mt-2">If you would like to check some rules or want to get help as registered user, please go to <a class="p-0" href="<%= help_and_rules_path %>">Help & Rules</a> page.</p>

  <h6 class="mt-3">Rules </h6>
  <p class="mt-2 m-0">- If someone has used any forbidden words in their comments, replies or reviews, you have right to delete it and ban the user. But, you have to specify the reason while banning the user.</p>
  <p class="mt-2 m-0">- You have right to ban a user if the user has reported comments more than five times without any valid reason.</p>
  <p class="mt-2 m-0">- You cannot delete any comments, replies or reviews if there is no valid reason.</p>

  <h6 class="mt-3">Adding a content</h6>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> Please go to <a class="p-0" href="<%= add_path %>">Add</a> page to choose whatever you would like to add to the application. </p>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> ! Before adding any anime or manga, please add its characters. </p>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0">After choosing the content to add, please pay attention to '<b>*</b>'. It means you have to fill that field to successfully create the content.</p>

  <ul class="list-unstyled pl-4 mt-2">
    <li>For adding a character</li>
        <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> Please pay attention to the information below the form. The rules are valid for editing a character form as well.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> If the character has some distinct attributes, for example hair color, you should add that attribute like this: </p>
        <p class="mt-2 ml-3 mb-0"> First, be sure that you have added '<b>+</b>' before each attribute name and attribute itself. For example: <b>+</b> hair color <b>+</b> light blue <b>+</b> power <b>+</b> shadow army...</p>
        <p class="mt-1 ml-3 mb-0"> After finishing writing down all the specific attributes for the character, if the character has general information as well, please use '<b>+</b>' again before the beginning of the information part. For example: <b>+</b> hair color <b>+</b> light blue <b>+</b> power <b>+</b> shadow army <b>+</b> He was lost in the middle of the mist when he lost all of his family members... </p>
  </ul>

  <h6 class="mt-3">Reports</h6>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> Please go to <a class="p-0" href="<%= reports_path %>">Reports</a> page to see all the reports that have been made by users. </p>

  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> You will see that all reports grouped by their reporters. If a user keeps reporting comments without any valid reason; you can keep the reports and after reaching five invalid reports, you can ban the user. Please remember to delete the reports after banning the user. </p>

  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> All reports include the reporter's name, the content which has the report, and the comment's writer's information in it as clickable links. <br> When you click to the name of the content, you will be directed to the content page. When a comment created, all its icons are in grey color. But, if a comment has been reported, the report icon's color will be red. (
        <svg class="icon" role="presentation">
          <use xlink:href="<%= asset_url("icons/icons-defs.svg" + "#reportDanger") %> "></use>
        </svg>)</p>

  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0">If the comment contains any forbidden words, when you delete the comment, all reports about that comment will disappear form Reports page.</p>

  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0">When you delete an invalid report, if there is any reports related to that comment, they will not be deleted. Also, the comment's report icon remains red.</p>

  <h6 class="mt-3">Making a registered user an admin</h6>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0"> If you want to promote a registered user to admin, to visit his/her profile page. You will see two buttons at the right top corner. The button for making that user an admin is 'Make Admin' button. <br>! Whenever you promote a user, you cannot take it back and you will not be able to block them any more.</p>

  <h6 class="mt-3">Unblocking a banned user</h6>
  <p class="mt-2 ml-2 mb-0">You can unblock a blocked user via 'unblock' button in their profile page.</p>

</div>
